sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant S as Server / CI Pipeline<br/>(sf CLI today)
    participant K as Private Key<br/>(your certificate pair)
    participant T as Salesforce<br/>Token Endpoint
    participant API as Salesforce<br/>REST API

    Note over S: Writes a tiny JSON claim:<br/>iss = consumer key, sub = username,<br/>aud = login.salesforce.com, exp = now + 3 min
    S->>K: Sign the claim (RSA SHA-256)
    K-->>S: Signed JWT — a tamper-proof "sealed letter"
    S->>T: POST /services/oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:jwt-bearer<br/>assertion=&lt;signed JWT&gt;
    T->>T: Verify signature with the app's uploaded<br/>X.509 certificate + check user is pre-authorized
    T-->>S: 200 OK — access_token (Bearer)<br/>NO refresh token — just sign a fresh JWT next time
    S->>API: GET /services/data/...<br/>Authorization: Bearer &lt;access_token&gt;
    API-->>S: JSON records

    Note over S,T: No secret ever crosses the network —<br/>only a signature the private key could have made
